%N A394921 Decimal expansion of the probability that a straight line drawn through a point uniformly selected at random on the surface of a cube, with a direction independently and uniformly selected at random, intersects the opposite face to the face on which the point lies.
%F A394921 Equals (2/Pi) * (2*sqrt(2) - sqrt(3) - 1 - 2 * log((2 + sqrt(2))/(1 + sqrt(3)))) + 1/3.
%F A394921 Equals (2/Pi) * (2*sqrt(2) - sqrt(3) - 1 + arccosh(2) - 2 * arcsinh(1)) + 1/3.
%F A394921 Equals (2/Pi) * (2*sqrt(2) - sqrt(3) - 1 + arctanh(sqrt(3)) + arctanh(1/sqrt(3)) - arctanh(sqrt(2)) - arcsinh(1)) + 1/3.
%F A394921 Equals (2/Pi) * (2*sqrt(2) - sqrt(3) - 1 - asinh(5 / sqrt(59 + 24 * sqrt(6)))) + 1/3.
%F A394921 Equals (2/Pi) * Integral_{x,y=0..1} arctan(x*y/sqrt(1 + x^2 + y^2)).
%F A394921 Equals (2/Pi) * Integral_{x,y=0..1} (1-x)*(1-y)/(1 + x^2 + y^2)^(3/2).
%F A394921 Equals A394922 / 3.
%e A394921 0.110890134315985242786328107446574279885713507473703...
%t A394921 RealDigits[(2/Pi) * (2*Sqrt[2] - Sqrt[3] - 1 - 2 * Log[(2 + Sqrt[2])/(1 + Sqrt[3])]) + 1/3, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A394921 (PARI) (2/Pi) * (2*sqrt(2) - sqrt(3) - 1 - 2 * log((2 + sqrt(2))/(1 + sqrt(3)))) + 1/3
